{{Quote|I never had a taste for this sort of thing. But I must admit, I'm deeply enjoying the suit!|Iron Monger to [[Iron Man]]|Iron Man (film)}}
*'''[[Iron Monger Armor]] Capabilities''': Stane had no superhuman abilities, instead using a powered suit of armor like [[Tony Stark]]'s. The [[Iron Monger Armor]] was reverse-engineered from the [[Iron Man Armor: Mark I|Mark I Armor]] and had many of the same capabilities as the [[Iron Man Armor: Mark III|Mark III Armor]]. However, it also had some design flaws inherited from the Mark I Armor, chiefly a dangerous icing problem that Stark had discovered when testing the [[Iron Man Armor: Mark II|Mark II]] but Stane only discovered during the [[Duel of Los Angeles]].
**'''Superhuman Strength''': [[File:Normal ironman 6087-1-.jpg|thumb|250px|Iron Monger lifting up an Audi Q7]] The Iron Monger armor gave Obadiah superhuman strength. Each arm of the suit was able to lift 7.5 tons.{{Ref|MSCE}} He used this strength to effortlessly throw [[Iron Man]] around. He also lifted a car and threw it at Iron Man with almost no effort put into the throw. Using pure strength, he also crushed Stark's armor to the point where it started sparking. He couldn't finish the job, however, since Stark had deployed knee flares.
**'''Superhuman Durability''': The Iron Monger armor could withstand ballistic weapons such as bullets and could sustain no damage towards crashing into walls or digging up concrete. [[Omnium Steel]], an alloy of incredible strength, was developed in Stark Industries' Sector 16, specifically for use in the Iron Monger suit. While boasted to be superior, the armor had weaknesses, such as not functioning at freezing temperatures of the upper atmosphere, as it would freeze over and suffer a complete shutdown, and many of its core mechanics and wiring was set up at places beneath the suit where it could be easily damaged, something Tony Stark exploited to disable its targeting system.
**'''Superhuman Speed''': With his upgrades to the [[Iron Man Armor: Mark I|Mark I Armor]], Stane put in a flight system and better thrusters that allowed him to almost catch up to [[Iron Man]] when the latter flew up towards the sky.
**'''Superhuman Stamina''': Like all [[:Category: Iron Man Armors|Iron Man Armors]], it took less energy in battle to punch, fly, and run. This allowed Stane to battle [[Iron Man]] for a long time.
**'''Superhuman Reflexes''': Although his heads up display wasn't as advanced as [[Tony Stark]]'s, Stane was still able to dodge many strikes by Iron Man. When battling Iron Man, Stane noticed a motorcycle drive by his legs and grabbed the motorcycle just in time to be able to hit his opponent with it.
**'''Flight''': [[File:IronMongerChasingIronMan.jpg|thumb|250px|Iron Monger chasing [[Iron Man]]]] Like Stark's Iron Man armor, Obadiah upgraded the flight capabilities of the Iron Monger suit, giving it flight jets powerful enough to lift the massive suit. The flight jets could either be used during standard operation in short bursts to allow the suit to jump small distances, or the thrusters could reconfigure into a form of flight mode to allow sustained flight.
**'''Power Suit''': The Iron Monger's onboard computer had little navigational focus, as the suit was based on Stark's Mark I, which had no computer system. Obadiah made smart targeting the HUD's primary component. However, the smart targeting was deemed useless when [[Iron Man]] ripped out the component from the back. Therefore, Stane had to resort to his own aim in order to fire shots at Stark. The armor was equipped with an arm gun that allowed him to shoot his opponents. However, the gun couldn't fire hard enough bullets to be able to penetrate Stark's last ditch arm shield.

===Abilities===
