{{Quote|Then, the passing of a titan. [[Howard Stark]]'s life long friend and ally [[Obadiah Stane]], steps in to help fill the gap left by the legendary founder.|[[Tony Stark]]'s award ceremony|Iron Man (film)}}
*'''Expert Businessperson''': An exceptional businessman who even [[Howard Stark]] acknowledged enough to make Stane his partner, Stane would later on prove fully capable of managing the position of CEO of [[Stark Industries]], maintaining the company at a high economic standing comparable to the rate with which his old friend had elevated the business to and slowly building the company's standing as a leading arms manufacturer. He would also become [[Tony Stark]]'s most prominent and trusted advisor once he took his rightful ownership of the company. While Stane was revealed to be practicing "dirty ethics" and selling weapons to both sides of war fronts including the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]], he was still highly successful in his endeavors, remaining undiscovered for a lengthy, but undetermined, amount of time.
*'''Expert Tactician''': [[File:Raza-with-obadiah.jpg|thumb|250px|Stane betrays [[Raza Hamidmi al-Wazar]]]] Stane felt jealous over [[Tony Stark]]'s reign because he had been working with [[Howard Stark]] longer. This caused Stane to figure out a master plan in order to take Tony Stark down. This included getting the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]] to kidnap Stark and kill him so that Stane can take over [[Stark Industries]] without having any blood on his hands. However, this plan backfired when the Ten Rings found out they were paid to kill Tony Stark. Later, Stark would break out using [[Iron Man Armor: Mark I|Iron Man Armor]]. This prompted Stane to change his plan so that he could betray the Ten Rings and utilize the armor to kill Stark instead. His plan only failed because Stark was more skilled in combat.
*'''Expert Engineer''': As a leading figurehead in the market of weapon sales, Stane was a well-versed expert in weapon design and weapons system engineering. Though not a natural prodigy on the level of [[Tony Stark]], Stane still had successfully created sufficiently advanced inventions that during his time as the CEO, he had already begun to elevate Stark Industries into a leading arms manufacturer. During the creation of the [[Iron Monger Armor]], Stane served as the lead supervisor, overseeing and designing the majority of the suit's layout, capabilities, and integrated weapons.
*'''Bilingualism''': Stane was fluent in his native English, as well as Urdu.

