{{Quote|Do you really think that just because you have an idea, it belongs to you? Your [[Howard Stark|father]], he helped give us the [[Atomic Bomb|atomic bomb]]. Now what kind of world would it be today if he was as selfish as you?|Obadiah Stane to [[Tony Stark]]|Iron Man (film)}}
*'''[[Iron Monger Armor]]''': [[File:IronMonger8-IM.png|thumb|250px|Iron Monger fires his missiles at [[Iron Man]]]] Obadiah Stane possessed the armor which derives from the [[Iron Man Armor: Mark I|Mark I armor]] he recovered from the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]]. It had powerful conventional weapons at his disposal including:
**'''Minigun''': Stane had it mounted on the right arm on the suit.
**'''Rocket Launcher''': Stane had it mounted on the left arm used to try to kill [[Tony Stark]].
**'''Shoulder-Armed Missile''': A missile launcher that was mounted on Stane's right shoulder.
{{Quote|You remember this one, right? It's a shame the government didn't approve it. There's so many applications for causing short-term paralysis.|Obadiah Stane to [[Tony Stark]]|Iron Man (film)}}
*'''[[Sonic Taser]]''': Stane carried around a sonic device that could be used to paralyze anyone exposed to it. Stane favored using this device as a means to hold people to his mercy, often paralyzing them before taking something of value from them for his own purposes, all the while taunting them before usually leaving them to die or be killed. Stane used the Sonic Taser first against [[Raza Hamidmi al-Wazar]], leaving him to die at the hands of Stane's men, and later against [[Tony Stark]], before taking Tony's [[Arc Reactor]] and using it to complete the Iron Monger armor.

==Facilities==
*'''[[Obadiah Stane's Mansion|Mansion]]''': Stane resided at this mansion where he watched the news.
*'''[[Stark Industries Headquarters]]''': As a chief officer of Stark Industries, Stane had his own private office. This is where he kept records of all his illegal activities. He once found [[Pepper Potts]] rummaging through his computer. He realized that she found his blueprints for his Iron Monger armor. He kept his armor in sector-16 of the building. Later, he battled [[Tony Stark]] outside of the headquarters and was killed when he fell into the headquarters' [[Arc Reactor]].
*'''[[Tony Stark's Mansion]]''': Due to his friendship with [[Tony Stark]], Stane visited him at his mansion several times. It is also the location of Stane's attempted murder on Stark where he stole his [[Arc Reactor]].

