==Trivia==
*In the comics, Obadiah Stane was the head of his own company and not a part of [[Stark Industries]], and also the first colleague of [[Norman Osborn]].
*Stane is seen playing chess, which is a reference to his comic book alter ego leading a supervillain team known as the [[w:c:marvel:Chessmen (Earth-616)|Chessmen]].

==Behind the Scenes==
*To prepare for the role of Iron Monger, [[Jeff Bridges]] grew a beard, shaved his head and {{WPS|Google|googled}} the {{WPS|Book of Obadiah}}, which led to his surprise upon learning that retribution is a major theme in that book of the {{WPS|Bible}}, something which Obadiah Stane represents.<ref>[http://www.scifijapan.com/articles/2008/04/30/iron-man-production-notes/ IRON MAN Production Notes]</ref> Bridges wrote backstory for Stane, believing "Obadiah" to not be his first name, but rather an alias he chose based on the book from the Bible.<ref>[https://www.cleveland.com/movies/2008/04/jeff_bridges_talks_iron_man_ro.html Jeff Bridges talks 'Iron Man,' Robert Downey Jr. and Obadiah]</ref>
*According to [[Jeff Bridges]], Obadiah Stane was initially scripted to survive at the end of ''[[Iron Man (film)|Iron Man]]'', with the Iron Monger armor being empty upon being opened. However, it was later decided to have Stane killed off.<ref>[https://www.ign.com/articles/2015/02/06/iron-mans-jeff-bridges-says-obadiah-stane-wasnt-originally-supposed-to-die IRON MAN'S JEFF BRIDGES SAYS OBADIAH STANE WASN'T ORIGINALLY SUPPOSED TO DIE]</ref>
*[[Loyd Catlett]] and [[Vince Deadrick Jr.]] were stunt doubles for [[Jeff Bridges]] in the role of Iron Monger.
*[[Jon Favreau]] thought of making the Iron Monger the main villain of ''[[Iron Man 2]]'', initially intending the [[Mandarin]] to be the villain of ''[[Iron Man (film)|Iron Man]]''. Stane was going to be Stark's friend and confidante in the first film, but then would become his enemy in the second installment. However, [[Mark Millar]] and Favreau were concerned about how to handle the Mandarin, so they reworked the character into a behind-the-scenes presence and made Iron Monger the first villain.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20121008192744/http://www.comicbookresources.com/?page=article&id=16292 LYING IN THE GUTTERS VOLUME 2 COLUMN 156]</ref>
*During early development of ''[[The Avengers]]'', [[Joss Whedon]] worried that [[Loki]] wouldn't be enough match to the [[Avengers]], Whedon had [[Ezekiel Stane]], Obadiah's son in the comics, fighting the Avengers alongside with Loki, but the idea was dropped due to [[Kevin Feige]]'s suggestion.<ref>[https://www.thrillist.com/entertainment/nation/the-avengers-battle-of-new-york-joss-whedon ''The Battle of New York: An 'Avengers' Oral History'']</ref>
*[[Soren Bendt Aaboe Pedersen]]'s storyboards for ''[[Doctor Strange in the Multiverse of Madness]]'' suggest that an alternate self of Iron Monger was going to be part of the [[Illuminati]] on Earth-838.<ref>[https://sorenbendt.com/project/7383/ ''Doctor Strange in the Multiverse of Madness'' - Storyboards by Soren Bendt]</ref>

